                <head>238. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Greek parliamentary elections were Held on May 11.
                        <persName>Karamanlis’</persName> National Radical Union (ERE) won 41 percent
                    of the vote and an absolute majority of 171 seats in the lower house. The
                    pro-Communist United Democratic Left (<gloss target="#t_EDA1">EDA</gloss>)
                    emerged as the second largest party with 79 seats. The centrist Liberal Party
                    lost heavily and retained only 36 seats.</p>
                <p>King <persName>Paul</persName> asked <persName corresp="#p_KK1"
                        >Karamanlis</persName> to form a new government, which took office on May
                    17. Telegram 3238 from Athens, May 21, analyzed the results of the elections.
                    (Department of State, Central Files, 781.00/5–2158)</p>
            </div>
